<section class="announcement">
  <h2>Black Lives Matter.</h2>
  <section class="description">
    <p>As a white man of privilege, I won't pretend that I'm qualified to speak on the matter—in fact, my inadequacies and naivety lends to my hesitation to stray out of silence.</p>
    <p>The brutal murder of George Floyd has been a catalyst for me—along with many others. I’m ready to speak up and do my part to help end police brutality and racial injustice—just saying <emphasis>I’m ready</emphasis> shows that my white privilege has no bounds.</p>
    <p>I’m here to help in whatever ways I can—I’ll make plenty of mistakes, but I’m listening. I’m working to become better educated on the matters. Donating where I can. Having conversations with friends and family. Voting. I'm aware what I'm doing isn't enough—and about 400 years too late, but I'm trying.</p>
    <p>I’m with you.</p>
  </section>
  <section class="links">
    <p>Below are some items I've found helpful in becoming more informed—maybe they will help you:
    <h3>Learn</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://blacklivesmatter.com/">#BlackLivesMatter</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.ibramxkendi.com/how-to-be-an-antiracist-1">How To Be An Antiracist by Ibram X. Kendi</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h8jUA7JBkF4">Uncomfortable Conversations with a Black Man</a></li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Donate</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://support.eji.org/give/153413/#!/donation/checkout">The Equal Justice Initiative</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.gofundme.com/f/georgefloyd">Official George Floyd Memorial Fund</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.gofundme.com/f/i-run-with-maud">I Run with Maud</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.communityjusticeexchange.org/nbfn-directory">National Bail Fund Network</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</section>
